org.spf4j.concurrent

Class UnboundedLoadingCache<K,V>

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.spf4j.concurrent.UnboundedLoadingCache<K,V>
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    com.google.common.cache.Cache<K,V>, com.google.common.cache.LoadingCache<K,V>, Function<K,V>

    @ParametersAreNonnullByDefault
public final class UnboundedLoadingCache<K,V>
extends Object
implements com.google.common.cache.LoadingCache<K,V>
    custom build high performance implementation for a unbounded guava cache: UnboundedLoadingCache is implemented with JDK concurrent map UnboundedLoadingCache2 is using the JDK 1.8 computing map functionality, but benchmarks show worse performance. Benchmark Mode Cnt Score Error Units CacheBenchmark.guavaCache thrpt 15 29011674.275 ± 710672.413 ops/s CacheBenchmark.spf4j2Cache thrpt 15 30567248.015 ± 807965.535 ops/s CacheBenchmark.spf4jCache thrpt 15 37961593.882 ± 1136244.254 ops/s CacheBenchmark.spf4jRacyCache thrpt 15 37553655.751 ± 855349.501 ops/s
    Author:
    zoly
